.TH BAUDZILLA232 1 "2025" "Baudzilla 1.0" "RS232 Test Tool"
.SH NAME
baudzilla232 \- RS232 bidirectional serial test tool

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B baudzilla232
[-v] <portA> <portB> [-r] [-m] [-sf file]
-b <baud> | --auto-baud
-n <loops> -t <timeout>
-l <logfile> -s <string>
[--test-iec101]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Baudzilla232 performs bidirectional RS232 testing between two ports
connected via a null modem cable. It sends a user defined test string
from A to B and from B to A, measures transfer time, and logs results.

Optional features include RTS/CTS flow control, modem signal display,
multi baud rate testing and a simple IEC 60870-5-101 probe on port A.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -v
Verbose output.

.TP
.B -r
Enable RTS/CTS hardware flow control.

.TP
.B -m
Show modem control signals.

.TP
.B -sf <file>
Write summary statistics to file.

.TP
.B -b <baud>
Specify baudrate (9600 19200 38400 57600 115200).

.TP
.B --auto-baud
Test all standard baudrates.

.TP
.B -n <loops>
Number of test loops.

.TP
.B -t <timeout>
Timeout seconds per direction.

.TP
.B -l <logfile>
Path to log output.

.TP
.B -s <string>
Test string to transmit.

.TP
.B --test-iec101
Run simple IEC101 probe on port A.

.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help and exit.

.SH EXAMPLE
baudzilla232 -v /dev/ttyS0 /dev/ttyS1 -b 9600 -n 5 -t 1 -l log.txt -s "Hello" --test-iec101

